{
  "texts": [
    "(A) Introduction to Artificial Intelligence in Biology:1.",
    "Overview of AI and its Applications: Artificial intelligence (AI) is a subfield of computer science that aims to mimic human intelligence and perform tasks similar to human abilities.",
    "It is closely related to data science, machine learning, and statistics.",
    "Artificial intelligence (AI) is the technical simulation of human intelligence using computerbased programs and robotics to mimic biological thought processes and physical expressions [1].",
    "It involves interdisciplinary application-oriented toolboxes such as machine learning, deep learning, robotics, gesture, facial expression, and cognitive and language processing."
  ]
}